<paragraph blockId="18.[192,1440,1551,1608]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,323,1551,1575]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</emphasis>
The all brown dorsum of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Gordon and Gonzalez" authorityYear="2019" box="[631,822,1551,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Pentilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dianna">
<emphasis box="[631,822,1551,1575]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Pentilia dianna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distinguish it from those species with black elytra. The male genitalia and 
<collectingCountry box="[483,580,1583,1607]" name="Guyana" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Guyana</collectingCountry>
<typeStatus box="[587,640,1584,1608]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
locality will further confirm an identification.
</paragraph>
